GLOBAL EPIDEMIOLOGY TRAINING POSITION, WHO, GENEVA
**************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed.html>
Date: Thu, 02 Jul 1998 10:15:52 +1000
From: Mahomed Patel <msp868@leprosy.anu.edu.au>

TEPHINET -- Training Programs in Epidemiology and Public Health Interventions
DUTY STATION: Geneva, Switzerland
ORGANIZATIONAL LOCATION: Division of Emerging and other Communicable
Diseases, Surveillance and Control (EMC), Unit of Disease Surveillance and
Control (DIS)
GENERAL OBJECTIVE:
In close collaboration with WHO, and within the TEPHINET Secretariat
located at both Atlanta (USA), and Geneva, to develop and maintain
efficient mechanisms to directly involve TEPHINET in international efforts
for disease surveillance and control.
DUTIES:
Under the authority of the TEPHINET Board and in close collaboration with
Chief, EMC/DIS, Geneva, as well as in close collaboration with the Atlanta
office of TEPHINET, achieve the following objectives:
Objective 1
Develop rapid/emergency response mechanisms
Tasks
1. In collaboration with the Executive Secretary, create a database of
expertise among trainees, trainers, graduates and TEPHINET member programmes
2. Ensure effective two-way communications between WHO/EMC and
participating programmes
3. Establish protocols for clearances (travel, permission, etc.) for
trainees and trainers
Objective 2
At WHO request, support coordination of response missions e.g. outbreak
investigations, establishing or evaluating surveillance systems
Tasks:
1. Build response teams in consultation with WHO/EMC, participating
programmes and partners
2. Ensure missions are documented in a timely fashion
3. Ensure missions are evaluated with respect to mission objectives,
exposure of TEPHINET to international work, and to specific training
objectives of TEPHINET programmes.
[There are 2 more objectives. Applications should be sent direct to the
address below, and not, repeat NOT, to ProMED-mail - Mod.JW]
